Web 1.0 - static web, limited one-way information and no user interaction[1]
web 2.0 - social web[1], users interact with the web platforms to share and exchange information
web 3.0 - next stage of the Internet, semantic web[1], intelligent machines and algorithms will be able to read data and understand the meaning from data such that users will have a more personalized experiences of using Internet.

Features of Web 3.0[1]:
intelligence - intelligent machines and algorithms used 
semantics - meaningful experiences of using the Internet 
ubiquitous - access the Internet anywhere, any time, and by anyone
virtualization - mix the experiences of physical and digital interaction 


